18/03/2004
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- NATO's Council of Permanent Representatives unanimously approved on Wednesday (17 March) Greece's request for assistance in ensuring security during the Summer Olympics in Athens. Greece made the request after last week's deadly terrorist attacks in Madrid. Greece's Permanent Representative to NATO Yiannis Zeppos thanked the Alliance for its solidarity and support. Greece has already spent an estimated 900m euros on security measures for the Games. (ANA, MPA - 17/03/04)
